Pre-Game Insights: Germany midfielder Aleksandar Pavlovic will be back from injury for their Nations League match against Netherlands.
Pavlovic and Angelo Stiller will form a midfield partnership.
Pavlovic is already a starting player for his club and only missed the Euros earlier this year due to illness.
Stiller made his international debut last month and would be making his third cap.
Nagelsmann praised the young players as prospects for the team ahead of the 2026 World Cup.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Germany drew 2-2 with the Dutch in Amsterdam in September.
Germany is currently top of Nations League Group A3 with seven points from three matches, with Netherlands second on five points.
